  "prompt": "How do you deposit cash at an ATM?",
  "response": "Depositing cash at an ATM is generally a straightforward process, but it can vary slightly depending on the bank and the ATM itself. Here's a general guide:\n\n**1. Find a Deposit-Accepting ATM:**\n\n*   **Check your bank's ATM locator:** Most banks have online tools or mobile apps to help you find ATMs that accept deposits.\n*   **Look for deposit indicators:** The ATM should be clearly marked as accepting deposits. It might have labels like \"Cash Deposits Accepted\" or show symbols related to deposits.\n\n**2. Prepare Your Cash:**\n\n*   **Straighten the bills:** Make sure the cash is flat, unfolded, and not crumpled. Wrinkled or damaged bills may be rejected.\n*   **Remove any paper clips, rubber bands, or other foreign objects.**\n*   **Count the bills:**  Know how much cash you're depositing.  This helps you verify the amount displayed on the screen later.\n\n**3. Insert Your Card and Enter PIN:**\n\n*   **Insert your debit or ATM card:** Follow the prompts on the screen to insert your card into the card reader.\n*   **Enter your PIN:** Enter your Personal Identification Number (PIN) when prompted.\n\n**4. Select Deposit Option:**\n\n*   **Choose \"Deposit\":**  On the ATM menu, select the \"Deposit\" option.  It might also be labeled as \"Cash Deposit\" or something similar.\n*   **Choose the Account:** Select the account you want to deposit the cash into (e.g., Checking, Savings).\n\n**5. Deposit Your Cash:**\n\n*   **Deposit Method:** There are typically two ways to deposit cash:\n    *   **Envelope Deposit (Older ATMs):**\n        *   The ATM will dispense an envelope.\n        *   Place the cash into the envelope.\n        *   Seal the envelope.\n        *   Insert the envelope into the designated slot.\n    *   **Cash Acceptor (Newer ATMs - \"Envelope-Free Deposit\"):**\n        *   The ATM will open a slot or drawer.\n        *   Carefully insert the stack of bills into the slot.  Make sure they are aligned properly.\n        *   The ATM will count the bills.\n\n**6. Verify the Deposit Amount:**\n\n*   **Confirm the Amount:** The ATM will display the amount of cash it has counted. **Carefully verify that this amount is correct.**\n    *   **If the Amount is Correct:**  Confirm the deposit.\n    *   **If the Amount is Incorrect:**  If the amount is wrong (e.g., it didn't count all the bills, or rejected some), there will usually be options to adjust the amount or cancel the transaction.  Follow the on-screen prompts.\n        *   **If Rejected:** The ATM will usually return the rejected bills. Check why they were rejected (too damaged, folded, etc.) and try again.\n\n**7. Complete the Transaction:**\n\n*   **Confirm the Deposit:** Once you've verified the amount, confirm the deposit.\n*   **Print Receipt:** The ATM will offer to print a receipt. Always take the receipt for your records. This is your proof of deposit, especially important if there are any discrepancies.\n*   **Remove Your Card:** Don't forget to take your card from the ATM. The ATM will usually beep or display a message to remind you.\n\n**8. Check Your Account Balance:**\n\n*   It's a good idea to check your account balance online or through your bank's app to confirm that the deposit has been credited to your account.  Note that it might not appear immediately; it could take a few hours or even until the next business day, depending on your bank's policies.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Safety:** Be aware of your surroundings when using an ATM, especially at night. Choose well-lit and populated ATMs.\n*   **ATM Fees:** Check if your bank charges fees for using ATMs, especially those not owned by your bank.\n*   **Deposit Limits:** Some ATMs may have limits on the amount of cash you can deposit at one time.\n*   **Malfunctions:** If the ATM malfunctions (e.g., it doesn't return your card, or keeps your deposit), contact your bank immediately.  Note the ATM location, date, time, and any error messages you saw.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to deposit cash at an ATM easily and securely. Remember that specific instructions may vary depending on the ATM and your bank. If you're unsure about any step, consult your bank's website or contact their customer service.\n",
